00:17:17.650 --> 00:17:19.710
I don't care about free users.

00:17:19.720 --> 00:17:20.850
I only want paid users.

00:17:20.860 --> 00:17:22.310
That's completely fine.

00:17:22.320 --> 00:17:24.680
That might be the right
decision for your business.

00:17:24.680 --> 00:17:27.520
But if that's the case,
100% do not choose

00:17:27.640 --> 00:17:28.940
freemium as your model.

00:17:28.940 --> 00:17:32.420
Because the most successful freemium
products in the App Store are

00:17:32.870 --> 00:17:37.630
providing a tremendous amount of
value to both free and paid users.

00:17:38.310 --> 00:17:41.170
And the reason why is that
the path to monetization in

00:17:41.170 --> 00:17:43.350
freemium is through engagement.

00:17:43.360 --> 00:17:46.880
And that means if the first
time a user launches your app,

00:17:46.950 --> 00:17:51.080
the first thing that they see is your
in-app store prompting them to pay,

00:17:51.080 --> 00:17:53.950
they're going to delete your app
and move on to something else.

00:17:53.960 --> 00:17:57.880
You're not doing yourself any
service at all by doing that.

00:17:58.000 --> 00:18:00.390
You need to give users
a chance to get engaged.

00:18:00.420 --> 00:18:03.150
And the way to do that in
a freemium product is by

00:18:03.360 --> 00:18:05.160
providing them value for free.

00:18:06.910 --> 00:18:08.860
Which brings us to the
next part of the funnel,

00:18:08.860 --> 00:18:10.620
which are your retained users.

00:18:10.700 --> 00:18:14.430
Obviously, this is a smaller percentage
than the number of users that

00:18:14.430 --> 00:18:16.650
download your app initially.

00:18:17.090 --> 00:18:20.350
And then the last piece of
the framework is do you have a

00:18:20.350 --> 00:18:22.540
plan to create lasting value?

00:18:22.640 --> 00:18:26.590
Again, the most successful freemium
products in the store are providing

00:18:26.600 --> 00:18:31.850
long-term value to their users via
the inherent qualities of the app

00:18:31.850 --> 00:18:36.390
themselves and as a developer through
a long-term roadmap to add features,

00:18:36.580 --> 00:18:38.230
content, or services.

00:18:38.370 --> 00:18:42.570
So if you've built something that is
only for periodic or one-time use,

00:18:42.760 --> 00:18:46.820
chances are freemium is not
the right model for you.

00:18:48.230 --> 00:18:49.680
Which again brings us to the
last piece of the funnel,

00:18:49.740 --> 00:18:50.560
