00:30:53.920 --> 00:30:56.040
So that's my discussion on localization.

00:30:56.120 --> 00:30:58.260
Last but not least,
and this is more or less a summary of

00:30:58.260 --> 00:31:02.880
everything I've talked about today,
how do you get featured in the App Store?

00:31:03.790 --> 00:31:06.640
First and foremost,
build something great,

00:31:06.670 --> 00:31:10.240
build something unique
that our customers love.

00:31:10.260 --> 00:31:13.420
Next, have a strong App Store presence.

00:31:13.440 --> 00:31:14.720
These things matter.

00:31:14.750 --> 00:31:17.530
When we feature an app,
we're putting our stamp of approval

00:31:17.530 --> 00:31:20.920
on it and we want everything,
not just the app itself,

00:31:20.920 --> 00:31:24.390
to look good and send a strong and
clear message to our customers.

00:31:25.720 --> 00:31:29.710
Choose the right business
model and price thoughtfully.

00:31:29.740 --> 00:31:32.760
Don't choose a business model or
a price that's out of line with

00:31:32.820 --> 00:31:35.590
a competitive marketplace for
apps that you're competing with.

00:31:35.600 --> 00:31:39.810
Offer your customers a universal binary.

00:31:39.820 --> 00:31:42.590
Again,
we've sold a lot of iPads and unless

00:31:42.640 --> 00:31:45.630
you're building something that
really is iPhone specific only,

00:31:45.970 --> 00:31:49.050
like a running app or a jogging app,
we strongly encourage you

00:31:49.050 --> 00:31:50.600
to build a universal app.

00:31:50.600 --> 00:31:53.540
Localize in relevant markets.

00:31:53.540 --> 00:31:56.600
And then lastly, let us know about it.

00:31:56.600 --> 00:31:58.880
It always helps to hear from the
developer what you've built and why

00:31:58.880 --> 00:32:02.600
you're proud of it and why you think
we should let our customers know.

00:32:02.600 --> 00:32:04.190
So that's my discussion.

