00:33:28.240 --> 00:33:31.570
I'll share with you some of the
resources we built to help you

00:33:31.580 --> 00:33:33.560
make great marketing campaigns.

00:33:33.640 --> 00:33:37.180
And then I'll conclude by talking
about the components that make up

00:33:37.180 --> 00:33:39.480
a comprehensive marketing campaign.

00:33:40.150 --> 00:33:42.840
So let's begin with the
programs and resources.

00:33:42.850 --> 00:33:46.590
Now I've been hearing for quite a while
that developers have been asking for a

00:33:46.600 --> 00:33:50.860
method to give away their paid apps for
free without making their apps freely

00:33:50.860 --> 00:33:52.910
available to everybody in the App Store.

00:33:52.920 --> 00:33:58.140
So I'm pleased to announce the
new App Store Code program.

00:33:58.760 --> 00:34:02.050
The App Store Code Program provides you,
the developer,

00:34:02.210 --> 00:34:08.930
the ability to market free offers to
customers using unique 12-digit codes.

00:34:09.430 --> 00:34:11.800
Currently,
the program is focused on offering

00:34:12.000 --> 00:34:14.990
paid apps downloaded for free.

00:34:15.240 --> 00:34:17.690
Now these codes are different
than the promo codes that you can

00:34:17.760 --> 00:34:19.600
request out of iTunes Connect.

00:34:19.830 --> 00:34:23.090
Those, which we'll talk about later,
should be used for PR.

00:34:23.530 --> 00:34:28.010
These codes should be used for
high volume marketing campaigns.

00:34:28.730 --> 00:34:30.600
It's a completely free program.

00:34:30.770 --> 00:34:34.900
You as a developer will waive your
70% royalty and we as Apple will

00:34:35.110 --> 00:34:37.750
waive our 30% commission.

00:34:37.990 --> 00:34:40.280
And when you receive these codes,
you can distribute them

00:34:40.280 --> 00:34:42.200
digitally or physically.

00:34:42.280 --> 00:34:45.060
I'll give you some examples
of this in a moment.

00:34:45.890 --> 00:34:48.360
So what are the benefits
of such a program?

00:34:48.370 --> 00:34:50.600
Well, first,
this will allow you to create

00:34:50.600 --> 00:34:55.130
an impactful and a high value
marketing promotion that's going to

00:34:55.150 --> 00:34:59.620
aid in not only user acquisition,
but also engagement.

00:34:59.890 --> 00:35:03.360
The fact that these codes
are integrated into iOS,

00:35:03.470 --> 00:35:07.370
it will create a simple, frictionless,
and a consistent user

00:35:07.430 --> 00:35:09.970
experience for those redeemers.

00:35:10.320 --> 00:35:13.620
So let me give you an example of what
one of these promotions could look like.

00:35:13.660 --> 00:35:17.200
And this is a test we did with
Big Fish Games where they wanted

00:35:17.200 --> 00:35:19.510
to distribute this offer digitally.

00:35:19.710 --> 00:35:23.430
Big Fish Games has a popular
game called Fairway Solitaire,

00:35:23.440 --> 00:35:27.570
and they wanted to target game
enthusiasts and golf enthusiasts,

00:35:27.680 --> 00:35:32.010
so they went after a few popular
websites that addressed that market.

00:35:32.300 --> 00:35:54.800
[ Transcript missing ]

00:35:55.370 --> 00:35:57.190
So back to the redemption flow.

00:35:57.320 --> 00:36:01.870
The customer taps on Get It Free,
at which point the App Store launches

00:36:02.330 --> 00:36:05.790
and the customer enters in their
password for the App Store.

00:36:06.160 --> 00:36:10.400
And that 12-digit code is automatically
populated in the redeem field.

00:36:10.490 --> 00:36:14.110
So all that the customer has to do
is tap redeem and the app begins

00:36:14.120 --> 00:36:16.320
downloading and the offer is complete.

00:36:18.800 --> 00:36:20.860
So that's an example of
a digital distribution.

00:36:20.890 --> 00:36:23.900
But here's an example of
a physical distribution.

00:36:23.920 --> 00:36:24.600
And this was great.

00:36:24.600 --> 00:36:28.310
Halfbrick came to us and they said,
we want to celebrate the

00:36:28.310 --> 00:36:31.290
anniversary of Fruit Ninja,
obviously a very popular game.

00:36:32.270 --> 00:36:37.090
And they wanted to do this by creating a
public event with a really high quality.

00:36:37.090 --> 00:36:40.300
And what they came to us
with is this idea of a kiosk.

00:36:41.130 --> 00:36:45.520
Where on this kiosk they had eight
iPads around the four corners of it

00:36:45.520 --> 00:36:50.290
with a flat screen and customers could
come up and play with Fruit Ninja.

00:36:50.770 --> 00:36:53.270
Now they would create signage
drawing people to this event.

00:36:53.390 --> 00:36:56.760
They would keep scores of the
day trying to find who was

00:36:56.760 --> 00:36:58.400
the best Fruit Ninja master.

00:36:59.390 --> 00:37:00.780
Well, we love this so much.

00:37:00.790 --> 00:37:04.020
They loved it so much they
created four of these kiosks and

00:37:04.020 --> 00:37:07.900
put them in public venues around
Melbourne and Sydney and shopping

00:37:07.920 --> 00:37:09.400
malls and parks and what have you.

00:37:09.400 --> 00:37:14.400
And it created a ton of PR buzz
and a lot of great engagement.

00:37:15.190 --> 00:37:20.170
Well, as people were playing Fruit Ninja,
they were given this little business

00:37:20.170 --> 00:37:25.400
card size collateral that each card
had its own unique 12-digit code on it.

00:37:26.300 --> 00:37:29.850
On the back, it explained to go into
the App Store and log in,

00:37:29.950 --> 00:37:33.340
type in that unique 12-digit
code and tap redeem.

00:37:33.400 --> 00:37:35.170
And again, the offer is complete.

00:37:35.360 --> 00:37:40.520
So this is a really great example of a
great physical campaign that drove live

00:37:40.520 --> 00:37:43.580
activation and Halfbrick really loved it.

00:37:44.400 --> 00:37:46.050
So if you have an idea
for such a campaign,

00:37:46.100 --> 00:37:47.940
we do have some requirements.

00:37:48.030 --> 00:37:50.920
First,
we're looking for you to create a high

00:37:50.920 --> 00:37:54.860
