00:47:48.560 --> 00:47:50.520
Now there are a number of
channels that I want you to

00:47:50.520 --> 00:47:53.280
consider in marketing your app.

00:47:53.320 --> 00:47:56.710
But I've bucketed them into
two different buckets for you.

00:47:57.030 --> 00:47:59.340
The first are owned channels.

00:47:59.350 --> 00:48:02.540
And in many cases,
these are free channels to you.

00:48:02.690 --> 00:48:07.080
So independent of your marketing budget,
you can be successful in these channels

00:48:07.730 --> 00:48:11.920
as long as you put enough energy and
do some great work to support those.

00:48:11.920 --> 00:48:13.820
And I'll conclude by talking
about some paid channels.

00:48:13.990 --> 00:48:15.760
So let's begin with social media.

00:48:15.760 --> 00:48:18.560
Now, through each of these channels,
I'm going to provide you some real

00:48:18.600 --> 00:48:22.150
great tips to really help you be
successful in these various areas.

00:48:22.400 --> 00:48:26.300
But with social media,
it should not be an afterthought.

00:48:26.380 --> 00:48:29.140
You need to think about how
you're going to integrate social

00:48:29.140 --> 00:48:31.810
media into not only your app,
but what your content

00:48:31.810 --> 00:48:33.290
strategy is going to be.

00:48:33.390 --> 00:48:36.000
So we'll start with the
integration with your app.

00:48:36.280 --> 00:48:38.800
And Alex touched on this first earlier.

00:48:38.970 --> 00:48:41.300
Use the share sheet that
we provide in iOS 7.

00:48:41.300 --> 00:48:45.050
That's probably the simplest way you
can get people to share content from

00:48:45.050 --> 00:48:47.380
within your app on Facebook and Twitter.

00:48:47.590 --> 00:48:50.770
But also think about how you can
leverage the social media networks

00:48:51.090 --> 00:48:53.300
to drive content back to your app.

00:48:53.330 --> 00:48:55.020
And I really like what
RunKeeper has done here.

00:48:55.560 --> 00:48:58.600
They give RunKeeper's customers,
their friends,

00:48:58.650 --> 00:49:01.210
the ability to cheer them on
as they're going for a run.

00:49:01.210 --> 00:49:04.490
By posting on Facebook or Twitter,
you can hear that as you're going for

00:49:04.600 --> 00:49:06.530
your run to help motivate you as you run.

00:49:06.950 --> 00:49:09.190
But then you need to think
about your content strategy.

00:49:09.230 --> 00:49:11.450
As you build out your
brand on social media,

00:49:11.560 --> 00:49:14.040
there's three things
I want you to think about.

00:49:14.180 --> 00:49:17.060
First, remember,
the content that you're putting

00:49:17.060 --> 00:49:20.330
out there is going to be nestled
amongst the content of your

00:49:20.390 --> 00:49:22.560
customers' friends and family.

00:49:22.560 --> 00:49:27.550
So be conversational, be engaging,
don't just continually try to sell, sell,

00:49:27.550 --> 00:49:28.170
sell.

00:49:28.170 --> 00:49:32.070
Make sure that your content would flow
within the newsfeed of your customers.

00:49:32.520 --> 00:49:35.570
And then think about how you can get
the customer to arrest the thumb.

00:49:36.520 --> 00:49:37.150
We all do this.

00:49:37.290 --> 00:49:39.460
We go through our newsfeeds very,
very quickly.

00:49:39.660 --> 00:49:40.830
But what is that bit of content?

00:49:40.980 --> 00:49:41.820
What is that copy?

00:49:41.990 --> 00:49:44.960
What is that photo that's going
to grab somebody's attention?

00:49:45.860 --> 00:49:47.530
And when you see something
like this from RunKeeper,

00:49:47.530 --> 00:49:49.180
you're thinking,
why is there a heart on here?

00:49:49.180 --> 00:49:51.080
Well,
you realize that you can go out there,

00:49:51.080 --> 00:49:53.550
this was celebrating a holiday,
but the fact that you can go

00:49:53.650 --> 00:49:56.560
out there and run this route,
I thought was a really engaging post.

00:49:57.960 --> 00:49:59.760
And when you're looking
for that engagement,

00:49:59.760 --> 00:50:02.320
you're trying to get your
customers to share your content.

00:50:02.320 --> 00:50:04.020
You want to drive that virality.

00:50:04.020 --> 00:50:06.220
But what do people want to share?

00:50:06.220 --> 00:50:10.200
Well, they share what's inspirational
to them or what's aspirational.

00:50:10.200 --> 00:50:13.040
So think about that copy
that does both that,

00:50:13.150 --> 00:50:14.730
inspires and aspires.

00:50:15.740 --> 00:50:16.140
So that's social media.

00:50:16.240 --> 00:50:17.160
Let's move forward to email.

00:50:17.420 --> 00:50:20.860
Email, in many cases,
is the first time you're going

00:50:20.900 --> 00:50:24.660
to be communicating with your
customer outside of the App Store.

00:50:24.660 --> 00:50:28.810
So think very hard about what that
first communication is going to be.

00:50:28.810 --> 00:50:30.240
You don't want to offend them.

00:50:30.360 --> 00:50:32.660
You don't want them to think
it's just a sales channel.

00:50:32.880 --> 00:50:35.220
You want them to keep you
out of their spam folder.

00:50:35.220 --> 00:50:37.770
So that first email is
extremely important.

00:50:37.780 --> 00:50:42.500
That second email, that third email,
put together a strong email campaign.

00:50:43.790 --> 00:50:45.940
and target your communications.

00:50:46.060 --> 00:50:47.720
There's two things you can do here.

00:50:47.830 --> 00:50:51.230
One, segment your subscriber base.

00:50:51.360 --> 00:50:54.100
Think about those emails you want to
send about maybe account management

00:50:54.100 --> 00:50:58.120
separately from those about app updates
depending on where you know your customer

00:50:58.120 --> 00:50:59.580
is in the life cycle of your app.

00:50:59.650 --> 00:51:03.060
But you also can target your
communications by platform.

00:51:03.060 --> 00:51:05.400
You know this is an
iPhone or an iPad user,

00:51:05.530 --> 00:51:08.140
so speak to them as an
iPhone or an iPad user.

00:51:08.140 --> 00:51:09.290
Alex Rofman

00:51:10.170 --> 00:51:12.080
Be useful.

00:51:12.210 --> 00:51:13.320
Don't continually try to sell.

00:51:13.560 --> 00:51:16.690
Think about the kind of content
you can provide in an email that's

00:51:16.830 --> 00:51:18.430
going to want that person to engage.

00:51:18.470 --> 00:51:22.410
I love this one from Trippet because
this is an email I definitely want.

00:51:22.490 --> 00:51:25.130
If my flight is going to be delayed,
I want to know that.

00:51:25.660 --> 00:51:29.260
Think about how you can support
your social media strategy.

00:51:29.320 --> 00:51:32.720
Provide links in your emails
allowing people to follow you on

00:51:32.720 --> 00:51:35.180
Facebook and Twitter or other networks.

00:51:35.190 --> 00:51:39.630
Optimize your email for the
devices it's being viewed on.

00:51:39.670 --> 00:51:42.840
Don't try to cram that large
desktop email into the small

00:51:42.840 --> 00:51:44.390
form factor in an iPhone.

00:51:44.590 --> 00:51:46.920
Use proper image sizes and font sizes.

00:51:46.920 --> 00:51:48.310
Next, let's talk about your website.

00:51:48.390 --> 00:51:51.870
I know you all have them,
but we introduced a technology in

00:51:51.930 --> 00:51:54.180
iOS 6 called Smart App Banners.

00:51:54.930 --> 00:51:58.320
I would love to see more of
you take advantage of this.

00:51:58.360 --> 00:52:01.260
You simply have to add one
line of code to your website.

00:52:01.320 --> 00:52:05.080
With that line of code,
it will detect when customers are

00:52:05.080 --> 00:52:07.630
coming to you from an iOS device.

00:52:07.780 --> 00:52:10.320
When that happens,
a banner ad is presented

00:52:10.320 --> 00:52:11.880
at the top of your page.

00:52:12.180 --> 00:52:15.770
And the call to action varies depending
upon where your customer is as far

00:52:15.860 --> 00:52:17.590
as their relationship with you.

00:52:17.740 --> 00:52:21.220
So in this case, if the customer does not
have Sky Guide installed,

00:52:21.220 --> 00:52:24.400
the call to action says View in
the upper right-hand corner.

00:52:24.400 --> 00:52:27.020
And when they tap on View,
they're taken into the

00:52:27.100 --> 00:52:28.840
App Store to download your app.

00:52:28.940 --> 00:52:31.630
Now if the customer does
have your app installed,

00:52:31.630 --> 00:52:32.470
it says Open.

00:52:32.470 --> 00:52:35.110
And when they tap on Open,
it launches your app.

00:52:44.170 --> 00:52:44.480
It's important to optimize
your website for the smaller

00:52:44.480 --> 00:52:44.480
form factor of the iPhone,
again, by using the proper image

00:52:44.480 --> 00:52:44.480
sizes and font sizes.

00:52:45.010 --> 00:52:47.480
And we encourage you to use
multiple install points.

00:52:47.640 --> 00:52:50.860
Again, use the App Store badge as a
call to action to get people to

00:52:50.860 --> 00:52:52.280
tap on it to download your app.

00:52:52.710 --> 00:52:55.700
Support that social media
strategy by allowing people

00:52:55.700 --> 00:52:57.500
to follow you on social media.

00:52:57.500 --> 00:53:00.470
And then finally,
include an FAQ and links to your customer

00:53:00.570 --> 00:53:04.440
care center so that customers can contact
you if there's an issue rather than

00:53:04.440 --> 00:53:06.780
leaving you bad reviews on the App Store.

00:53:07.500 --> 00:53:09.690
So the next channel is cross promotion.

00:53:09.690 --> 00:53:13.940
Now for you developers in the audience
that have multiple apps on the App Store,

00:53:14.130 --> 00:53:17.820
you are at a severe advantage to those
that don't because you already have

00:53:17.820 --> 00:53:19.970
an audience that you can speak to.

00:53:19.980 --> 00:53:24.460
But please, be thoughtful when you're
cross promoting your apps.

00:53:26.000 --> 00:53:28.200
The More Apps menu is a
popular way of doing it,

00:53:28.240 --> 00:53:30.060
and I like how Yahoo has done this.

00:53:30.110 --> 00:53:33.070
By tapping on the hamburger menu,
they are then presenting

00:53:33.070 --> 00:53:36.640
all the Yahoo apps,
which then the customer can then tap on,

00:53:36.640 --> 00:53:39.280
and then they're taken directly
into the App Store to download.

00:53:39.280 --> 00:53:40.920
It's a very thoughtful implementation.

00:53:43.470 --> 00:53:45.680
We also see the use of tickers now.

00:53:45.680 --> 00:53:47.420
And this is an example
with the Sims Free Play.

