I really like what I'm

00:55:52.020 --> 00:55:53.380
seeing with app trailers.

00:55:53.450 --> 00:55:55.730
They are really been taken
to the next level with a

00:55:55.730 --> 00:55:57.580
really high production value.

00:55:57.580 --> 00:56:00.890
But because I'm seeing so many of them,
it's really important that you

00:56:00.890 --> 00:56:02.440
follow a few tips and tricks.

00:56:03.100 --> 00:56:07.440
The first thing is to think about those
first six seconds of your trailer.

00:56:07.440 --> 00:56:10.600
You don't need to open your trailer
with your company logo and your

00:56:10.600 --> 00:56:12.740
license source logo and various things.

00:56:13.620 --> 00:56:16.020
Get into the beauty of your app to get
people to want to watch your videos.

00:56:16.240 --> 00:56:17.000
And then watch the rest of your trailer.

00:56:17.030 --> 00:56:19.500
Keep your trailer to
about 30 to 60 seconds,

00:56:19.500 --> 00:56:22.170
because that's about all the
time you have to keep somebody's

00:56:22.300 --> 00:56:23.800
attention span on a trailer.

00:56:25.350 --> 00:56:29.130
And then use professional
capturing tools.

00:56:29.280 --> 00:56:31.490
Gone are the days where your friend
sits over your shoulder with a

00:56:31.500 --> 00:56:34.920
camcorder trying to watch you record
your experience on the iPhone.

00:56:34.920 --> 00:56:37.730
Use digital capturing tools,
and there's a number of really great

00:56:37.730 --> 00:56:39.380
ones out there in the market today.

00:56:39.380 --> 00:56:43.640
And support that capture
with a great soundtrack.

00:56:44.240 --> 00:56:47.310
Whether it's music or a voiceover,
that is really going to

00:56:47.310 --> 00:56:49.090
add a lot to your trailer.

00:56:49.090 --> 00:56:51.740
You're going to want to
provide a clear call to action.

00:56:51.740 --> 00:56:55.830
And then finally,
ensure that your trailer

00:56:55.960 --> 00:56:57.560
is globally appropriate.

00:56:57.800 --> 00:56:59.600
And there's two aspects of this.

00:56:59.660 --> 00:57:01.850
First is price.

00:57:01.910 --> 00:57:04.440
If you market the app here
and saying that it's in so

00:57:04.440 --> 00:57:07.880
many euros or what have you,
that doesn't mean a lot to an American or

00:57:07.970 --> 00:57:11.050
somebody in Japan or what have you,
because they don't understand

00:57:11.060 --> 00:57:12.300
the currency conversion.

00:57:12.300 --> 00:57:16.120
But also, that's going to limit you to do
any price promotions in the future.

00:57:16.120 --> 00:57:20.650
So I just recommend leaving pricing
out of your trailer unless your app

00:57:20.870 --> 00:57:25.170
The second component to globally
appropriateness is the content.

00:57:25.410 --> 00:57:28.200
The levels of offensive
content vary around the globe,

00:57:28.200 --> 00:57:32.760
